Docs.summary: The is used to receive data from Service Bus Queues and Subscriptions. When sending messages, the is used.
Docs.remarks: The message structure is discussed in detail in the product documentation.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ApplicationProperties As IReadOnlyDictionary(Of String, Object)

Docs.summary: Gets the application properties bag, which can be used for custom message metadata.
Docs.remarks: Only the following value types are supported: byte, sbyte, char, short, ushort, int, uint, long, ulong, float, double, decimal, bool, Guid, string, Uri, DateTime, DateTimeOffset, TimeSpan

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Body As BinaryData

Docs.summary: Gets the body of the message.
Docs.remarks: To be added.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentType As String

Docs.summary: Gets the content type descriptor.
Docs.remarks: Optionally describes the payload of the message, with a descriptor following the format of RFC2045, Section 5, for example "application/json".

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CorrelationId As String

Docs.summary: Gets the correlation identifier.
Docs.remarks: Allows an application to specify a context for the message for the purposes of correlation, for example reflecting the MessageId of a message that is being replied to. See Message Routing and Correlation.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DeadLetterErrorDescription As String

Docs.summary: Gets the dead letter error description for the message.
Docs.remarks: To be added.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DeadLetterReason As String

Docs.summary: Gets the dead letter reason for the message.
Docs.remarks: To be added.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DeadLetterSource As String

Docs.summary: Gets the name of the queue or subscription that this message was enqueued on, before it was dead-lettered.
Docs.remarks: Only set in messages that have been dead-lettered and subsequently auto-forwarded from the dead-letter queue to another entity. Indicates the entity in which the message was dead-lettered. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DeliveryCount As Integer

Docs.summary: Get the current delivery count.
Docs.remarks: Number of deliveries that have been attempted for this message. The count is incremented when a message lock expires, or the message is explicitly abandoned by the receiver. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EnqueuedSequenceNumber As Long

Docs.summary: Gets the original sequence number of the message.
Docs.value: The enqueued sequence number of the message.
Docs.remarks: For messages that have been auto-forwarded, this property reflects the sequence number that had first been assigned to the message at its original point of submission. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EnqueuedTime As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the date and time of the sent time in UTC.
Docs.remarks: The UTC instant at which the message has been accepted and stored in the entity. This value can be used as an authoritative and neutral arrival time indicator when the receiver does not want to trust the sender's clock. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ExpiresAt As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the date and time in UTC at which the message is set to expire.
Docs.value: The message expiration time in UTC. This property is read-only.
Docs.remarks: The UTC instant at which the message is marked for removal and no longer available for retrieval from the entity due to expiration. Expiry is controlled by the property and this property is computed from +
Docs.exception: If the message has not been received. For example if a new message was created but not yet sent and received.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public hidebysig instance class Azure.Core.Amqp.AmqpAnnotatedMessage GetRawAmqpMessage() cil managed

Docs.summary: Gets the raw Amqp message data that was transmitted over the wire. This can be used to enable scenarios that require reading AMQP header, footer, property, or annotation data that is not exposed as top level properties in the .
Docs.remarks: To be added.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LockedUntil As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the date and time in UTC until which the message will be locked in the queue/subscription.
Docs.value: The date and time until which the message will be locked in the queue/subscription.
Docs.remarks: For messages retrieved under a lock (peek-lock receive mode, not pre-settled) this property reflects the UTC instant until which the message is held locked in the queue/subscription. When the lock expires, the is incremented and the message is again available for retrieval. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LockToken As String

Docs.summary: Gets the lock token for the current message.
Docs.remarks: The lock token is a reference to the lock that is being held by the broker in ReceiveMode.PeekLock mode. Locks are used to explicitly settle messages as explained in the product documentation in more detail. The token can also be used to pin the lock permanently through the Deferral API and, with that, take the message out of the regular delivery state flow. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property MessageId As String

Docs.summary: Gets the MessageId to identify the message.
Docs.remarks: The message identifier is an application-defined value that uniquely identifies the message and its payload. The identifier is a free-form string and can reflect a GUID or an identifier derived from the application context. If enabled, the duplicate detection feature identifies and removes second and further submissions of messages with the same MessageId.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property PartitionKey As String

Docs.summary: Gets a partition key for sending a message to a partitioned entity.
Docs.value: The partition key. Maximum length is 128 characters.
Docs.remarks: For partitioned entities, setting this value enables assigning related messages to the same internal partition, so that submission sequence order is correctly recorded. The partition is chosen by a hash function over this value and cannot be chosen directly. For session-aware entities, the property overrides this value.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ReplyTo As String

Docs.summary: Gets the address of an entity to send replies to.
Docs.remarks: This optional and application-defined value is a standard way to express a reply path to the receiver of the message. When a sender expects a reply, it sets the value to the absolute or relative path of the queue or topic it expects the reply to be sent to. See Message Routing and Correlation.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ReplyToSessionId As String

Docs.summary: Gets a session identifier augmenting the address.
Docs.value: Session identifier. Maximum length is 128 characters.
Docs.remarks: This value augments the ReplyTo information and specifies which SessionId should be set for the reply when sent to the reply entity. See Message Routing and Correlation

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ScheduledEnqueueTime As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Gets the date and time in UTC at which the message will be enqueued. This property returns the time in UTC; when setting the property, the supplied DateTime value must also be in UTC.
Docs.value: The scheduled enqueue time in UTC. This value is for delayed message sending. It is utilized to delay messages sending to a specific time in the future.
Docs.remarks: Message enqueuing time does not mean that the message will be sent at the same time. It will get enqueued, but the actual sending time depends on the queue's workload and its state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property SequenceNumber As Long

Docs.summary: Gets the unique number assigned to a message by Service Bus.
Docs.remarks: The sequence number is a unique 64-bit integer assigned to a message as it is accepted and stored by the broker and functions as its true identifier. For partitioned entities, the topmost 16 bits reflect the partition identifier. Sequence numbers monotonically increase. They roll over to 0 when the 48-64 bit range is exhausted. This property is read-only.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property SessionId As String

Docs.summary: Gets the session identifier for a session-aware entity.
Docs.value: The session identifier. Maximum length is 128 characters.
Docs.remarks: For session-aware entities, this application-defined value specifies the session affiliation of the message. Messages with the same session identifier are subject to summary locking and enable exact in-order processing and demultiplexing. For session-unaware entities, this value is ignored. See Message Sessions.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property State As ServiceBusMessageState

Docs.summary: Gets the state of the message.
Docs.remarks: The state of the message can be Active, Deferred, or Scheduled. Deferred messages have Deferred state, scheduled messages have Scheduled state, all other messages have Active state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Subject As String

Docs.summary: Gets an application specific label.
Docs.remarks: This property enables the application to indicate the purpose of the message to the receiver in a standardized fashion, similar to an email subject line. The mapped AMQP property is "subject".

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property TimeToLive As TimeSpan

Docs.summary: Gets the message’s "time to live" value.
Docs.value: The message’s time to live value.
Docs.remarks: This value is the relative duration after which the message expires, starting from the instant the message has been accepted and stored by the broker, as captured in . When not set explicitly, the assumed value is the DefaultTimeToLive for the respective queue or topic. A message-level value cannot be longer than the entity's DefaultTimeToLive setting and it is silently adjusted if it does. See Expiration

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property To As String

Docs.summary: Gets the "to" address.
Docs.remarks: This property is reserved for future use in routing scenarios and presently ignored by the broker itself. Applications can use this value in rule-driven auto-forward chaining scenarios to indicate the intended logical destination of the message.

Docs.summary: Gets a partition key for sending a message into an entity via a partitioned transfer queue.
Docs.value: The partition key. Maximum length is 128 characters.
Docs.remarks: If a message is sent via a transfer queue in the scope of a transaction, this value selects the transfer queue partition: This is functionally equivalent to and ensures that messages are kept together and in order as they are transferred. See Transfers and Send Via.
